FBIS4-41816 "drsov124_f_94024" FBIS-SOV-94-124 Daily Report 27 Jun 1994 National Affairs 61 Percent of District Voters Against Nuclear Station 61 Percent of District Voters Against Nuclear Station LD2706170394 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1612 GMT 27 Jun 94 LD2706170394 Moscow INTERFAX English BFN [Text] A total of 61 percent of voters of the Ukrainian Zaporozhye Region Kamensk-Dneprovsk District have voted against the utilization of the sixth block of the Zaporozhye Nuclear Power Station. A total of 38 percent of voters voted for it during a referendum held along with the presidential and local elections in Ukraine. Voters were asked whether it was reasonable to switch on the sixth block before a law on nuclear energy was adopted. The ballot papers also included a question on whether a storage facility for exhaust nuclear fuel could be built in the region. An INTERFAX correspondent reports that 32 percent of voters were in favor of such a facility for exhausted nuclear fuel and 63 percent were against. A total of 68 percent of the voters registered in the region took part in the referendum. This referendum was initiated by the District Council.
